featured_reviews.review_id:
So, will I be able to review the place of almighty (though created by us humans)? I am a nature worshipper, I worship the elements that my body is made of. I can't even go to debates on the existence of the supreme power or authority we know as God.

However, this review is a chance to help people know how inclusive is the culture still. We just can't believe why people fight. Because, if I tell you, the Masjid is at a distance of 3 steps from the Hanuman temple (facing it), on the right, one lokenath baba temple, Durga murti bhasan ghat where chathh puja is celebrated on the left is Kali stans...

It is an amazing feeling crossing that street.  What I learnt is, every religion can exist together, the only thing which is required is: Respect.

Visit the place if not the masjid...Buri Dihing river is crossing the town... beside the street. You can take the local boat (the wooden one) as well. (When we were Young, we used to travel using the banana plant,the boat made of bamboos and various banana tree. the river banks. (both sides) are covered with berries, various species of the Flora and fauna.
